Rating: 4
I have made this recipe a number of times with rave reviews. The type of balsamic vinegar is what makes it so delicious. I use Villa Manodori dark cherry balsamic vinegar, available at Williams Sonoma. It is a splurge but is totally worth it!

Rating: 3
Surprisingly good. I made with just a little less pepper but with the full amount of the balsamic. To my husband, a little less pepper would have been better while I thought it was fine. To me, less balsamic would've been better but he thought it was just right. Long story short, you will have to try it as is the first time and make your adjustments the next time. I served it over mascarpone and thought it was very good. I will serve it with homemade vanilla ice cream next time. Yes, there will be a next time.

Rating: 3
I made this on the Fourth of July and was a little worried about the response I would get from it. Everyone loved it and wanted the recipe! It is important to point out that I went a little easy on the pepper and vinegar, just to be safe. Served with vanilla ice cream.

